Package: EvalEmulateSurv
Title: Evaluation of Emulated Survival Individual Patient Data
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person(given  = "Gosuke",
           family = "Homma",
           role   = c("aut", "cre"),
           email  = "my.name.is.gosuke@gmail.com"),
    person(given  = "Eamonn",
           family = "Bolger",
           role   = c("aut")),
    person(given  = "Annie",
           family = "Wang",
           role   = c("aut")))
Description: Provides tools to evaluate how well emulated individual patient
    data (IPD) reproduces the original IPD in terms of survival endpoints.
    Three complementary metrics are implemented: the Normalised Area Under the
    Curve (NAUC), the Kolmogorov-Smirnov (K-S) distance, and the Root Mean
    Square Error (RMSE) between Kaplan-Meier survival curves. Metrics can be
    computed for the overall population and for subgroups defined by single
    variables or N-way interaction terms. Results are summarised via a
    dedicated S3 class with formatted plain-text and kable output.
